  <notes>
  <p>
  This is not a bad little beer.  I'm drinking it now after 10 months
  and it's quite nice.  I can't believe it's 30+ IBUs, though.  And
  looking at the log, we didn't record one of the hop additions...
  Anyway, the colour is beautiful.  It's a dark reddish brown.  Just
  enough roastiness to make it nice.  Not quite to style since it
  should probably use chocolate, but I don't care.  The roast barley
  goes well with the german hops.  As you can probably tell, this
  was a "throw in what you've got" recipe.  However, we voted on the
  hops based on what we thought smelled nice.  Thus the strange hop
  schedule.  It's a bit muddy and I would get rid of the Goldings
  next time.  Also, I don't like the yeast.  I'd go with K97 next time.
  </p>
